Analysis — Avg Revenue per Paying User by Country

The chart shows average revenue per paying user by country using subscription events.

US leads with $25.07, followed by NL with $22.38, while TR is lower at $13.31.

Insight

US and NL users generate higher value per user, likely due to better retention or higher plan adoption.
TR users contribute less revenue per user, which may indicate lower pricing, shorter retention, or higher churn.

Business Takeaway

US/NL = high-value markets (focus on retention & upsell)
TR = growth/price-sensitive market (optimize conversion & pricing)